data.content:
All working. Here's the summary:

| API | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `options.GetTypeInfo<T>()` | Returns `JsonTypeInfo<T>` directly — no cast needed. Throws if metadata isn't available. |
| `options.TryGetTypeInfo<T>(out JsonTypeInfo<T>?)` | Returns `bool`; gives you the typed metadata via `out` without throwing. |

The key lines:

```csharp
// Strongly-typed retrieval (throws if unavailable)
JsonTypeInfo<Person> personInfo = options.GetTypeInfo<Person>();

// Safe probe — no exception, just returns false
if (options.TryGetTypeInfo<int>(out JsonTypeInfo<int>? intInfo))
    // use intInfo
else
    // not available
```

Both require .NET 11+ (`net11.0`) and a `TypeInfoResolver` configured on the options (e.g., `new DefaultJsonTypeInfoResolver()` for reflection-based resolution).
